In [[mathematics]], the '''Faltings height''' of an [[abelian variety]] defined over a [[number field]] is a measure of its arithmetic complexity. It was introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Faltings|authorlink=Gerd Faltings|year=1983}}  in his proof of the [[Mordell conjecture]].

